BUILDING\n2400 Byberry Road, Bensalem, PA 19020\nHours: First Wednesday of every month 9am-noon\nWARMINSTER COMMUNITY PARK (WCP)\n(Located in the blue trailer located with the Parks and Recreation office and the Warminster Tax Collector’s office)\n1100 Veterans Way\nWarminster, PA 18974\nHours: Second Wednesday of every month 9am-noon\nWARRINGTON TOWNSHIP BUILDING\n852 Easton Road, Warrington, PA 18976\nHours: Third Wednesday of every month 9am-noon\nWARWICK TOWNSHIP BUILDING\n1733 Township Greene, Jamison, PA 18929\nHours: Fourth Wednesday of every month 9am-noon\nFacebook Feed\nSenator Frank Farry\nFamily Fun Day 2026\nFamily Fun Day 2026\nFamily Fun Day 2026\nI was proud to join Michael Eckert, Neshaminy QB class of ’26, at the Capitol.\nI was honored to be named the State Official of the Year from Life Sciences PA at their Annual Dinner on March 11.\nAmerican Cancer Society Cancer Action Network PA Legislative Champion Award\nSB 99 – My Breast Cancer Imaging Bill Passes House – heads to Governor’s desk\n2025 Langhorne Athletic Association 8u Baseball Middle Atlantic Regional Champs\n2025 Student Government Day with Conwell-Egan Catholic High School\n2025 Diwali Celebration at the Capitol\n2025 Senator for a Day\n2025 Senator for a Day\nCapitol Fountain Turns Pink for Breast Cancer Awareness Month and promoting SB88\nTurning the Fountain Pink for Breast Cancer Awareness Month and promoting SB88\n2025 Senior Expo\n2025 Senior Expo\n2025 Senior Expo\n2025 Senior Expo\nPress Conference with PA Treasury on Unclaimed Property\nFirst Institutional Sustainability and Innovation Committee Meeting\nCelebrating Senate Bill 88 Passing Senate\nCelebrating the Eagles Super Bowl at The Capitol\nMay 6, 2025 – Chief Wiegman served as Guest Chaplain during Police Memorial Week\nOctober 25, 2024 – 2024 Senator For a Day\nOctober 22, 2024 – Holy Ghost Prep Baseball Team celebrating their 2024 State Championship\nOctober 21, 2024 – Eagle Scout Christopher Carroll\nOctober 10, 2024 – 2024 Senior Expo\nOctober 10, 2024 – 2024 Senior Expo\nOctober 10, 2024 – 2024 Senior Expo\nOctober 1, 2024 – Breast Cancer Coalition Pink Fountain Press Conference\nOctober 1, 2024 – Newtown AA 12U celebrating their run in the Little League Word Series\nSeptember 23, 2024 – Ensign Sarah Mitchell Bridge Dedication\nSeptember 23, 2024 – Ensign Sarah Mitchell Bridge Dedication\nSeptember 30, 2024 – Jay Ferraro was raising awareness for Ovarian Cancer and his foundation.\nMay 8, 2024 – I welcomed and honored Payton Hinkle, Julia Horger, and Grace Nesbitt at the Capitol for competing in the PIAA Girls Wrestling State Championship, placing 5th, 1st, and 2nd in their weight class respectfully.\nMarch 18, 2024 – Collin Goetter, an offensive lineman for Central Bucks South High School was named to the Big 33 roster for Team PA.  We welcomed Collin and his parents at the Capitol.\nMay 7, 2024 – The Archbishop Wood Girls Basketball Team, were recognized and honored for their fourth straight PIAA State Class 5A Championship at the Capitol.\nReps. Kristin Marcell and Joe Hogan joined me in welcoming to the Capitol the 2023 PIAA Girls Tennis State Champs from Council Rock South High School.\nApril 19, 2024 The Trenton Road Bridge in Middletown Township was named “Staff Sgt. Jae S. Moon Memorial Bridge” in honor of a local  U.S. Army soldier who was killed in action in action in Iraq in 2006.  I am pictured here with State Rep, Joe Hogan and Staff Sgt. Jae S. Moon’ sister Crystal and his parents.\nRandy Seitter, a local veteran advocated for the creation of a special Air Medal license plate process through PennDOT and I am honored that I was able to change the law for him and all the Air Medal recipients.\nSeptember 19, 2023 – Sen. Robinson and I with former Prisoner of War and Army Private First Class, Jessica Lynch.\nMay 3, 2023 – I had the honor of having Father Mykola Ivanov, pastor of St. Anne’s Ukrainian Catholic Church in Warrington as a guest chaplain at the Capitol\nMay 3, 2023 – I was proud to welcome the Archbishop Wood High School Girls Basketball Team to the Capitol to celebrate their state championship.\nJanuary 3, 2023 – Sen. Farry and his wife and children at the swearing-in ceremony\nJanuary 3, 2023 – Sen. Farry being sworn into the Senate of Pennsylvania\nMarch 8, 2023 – Sen. Farry, Chairman Urban Affairs and Housing Committee speaks at first committee meeting\nSeptember 28,2023 – Sen. Farry speaking with constituents at his Senior Expo\nOctober 27, 2023 – Sen. Farry poses with some of the high school ‘senators’ at his ‘Senator For a Day’ event\nOctober 27, 2023 – Sen. Farry engaging with students at his ‘Senator For a Day’ event\nOctober 27, 2023 – Sen. Farry speaking to high school students at his ‘Senator For a Day’ event\nSeptember 28,2023 – Sen. Farry speaking at a press conference introducing legislation to combat crime\nMeet Frank Farry\nFrank Farry was elected to the Senate of Pennsylvania in November 2022 to represent the 6th Senate District after serving in the House of Representatives for seven terms. Part of his advocacy focuses on the first responder community, ensuring a quality education, and protecting our taxpayers. A lifelong resident of Bucks County, Farry has been serving his community his entire career.  He has been the chief of Langhorne-Middletown Fire Company since 2001, and a member of the organization for over three decades.\nLearn More",
