    "title": "E-news Updates – June 23, 2026",
    "url": "https://senatorfarry.com/enews/062326-2/",
    "date": null,
    "raw_text": "E-news Updates - June 23, 2026 - Senator Farry\nView this email in a browser\nIn this Update:\nThe PFC George Raymond Huntzinger Memorial Bridge (Brownsville Rd.) is Now Open\nDax’s 6th Birthday\n2026 Woods Services Humanitarian Award\nBAPS Charities Spirit of Service Walk/Runs\nSave The Date for Our Senior Expo\nThe PFC George Raymond Huntzinger Memorial Bridge (Brownsville Rd.) is Now Open\nI am pleased to announce the Brownsville Road Bridge over Neshaminy Creek connecting Middletown and Lower Southampton townships reopened five months ahead of schedule and a $1 million less cost to taxpayers.\nPrior to the reopening this past Thursday, I joined Rep. Hogan, Matt Allen, Bucks County Veterans Affairs, Ed Preston, chairman PA Vietnam Veterans Memorial Fund, Din Abazi, P.E., District Executive PennDOT, Kevin Loftus, President & CEO, Loftus Construction, local veterans and community members for a rededication ceremony in honor of PFC George Raymond Huntzinger, who gave his life during the Vietnam War. The bridge was originally dedicated in August 2023 before PennDOT began construction to replace the bridge in spring 2025.\nHuntzinger, a Langhorne resident, began his tour of duty with the US army on September 11, 1969, and less than two months later on October 29th he tragically lost his life on October while dismantling a landmine in Vietnam. PFC Huntzinger will forever be remembered and honored in our community.\nNote: Drone photo supplied by Pennsylvania Department of Transportation (PennDOT)\nYou can view the full ceremony here\n.\nDax’s 6th Birthday\nI was grateful to attend Dax’s Day to celebrate and honor Dax Babcock’s 6th Birthday.\nAfter the Babcock family lost Dax at age 2 in a tragic accident, they created the\nDax Pact\nto honor his memory and engage others to live big and love hard just like Dax.\nTheir foundation is doing remarkable work in Dax’s memory by investing in public parks, donating toy cars and trucks to kids in need, and providing annual scholarships to local daycares and camps.\n2026 Woods Services Humanitarian Award\nI was proud to honor Kimberly Permar, Executive Director of Bucks County Health Improvement Partnership (BCHIP), with a Pennsylvania Senate citation for being named the 2026 Woods Humanitarian at Woods System of Care Run earlier this month.\nKim’s advocacy on behalf of Woods System of Care projects has increased access to mental health services and attainable housing across Bucks County. This award is a testament to her dedication as she truly exemplifies the spirit of community.\nKimberly and I are pictured here with Woods System of Care President and CEO Tine Hansen-Turton and Woods System of Care Senior Executive VP/Chief Legal and Governance Officer Simon Kimmelman.\nBAPS Charities Spirit of Service Walk/Runs\nI was proud to join two BAPS Charities Spirit of Service Walk-Runs during the last weekend of May.\nThe first event was held at Falls Township Community Park supporting the Middletown Community Foundation. The next morning, Lions Pride Park in Warrington hosted the event benefiting the Warrington Township Police Department Shop with a Cop program.\nBAPS Charities does an incredible job bringing people together through service and support for local communities. Thank you to everyone who walked, ran, volunteered, and contributed to these great causes.\nSave The Date for Our Senior Expo\nOur annual Senior Expo will be held on September 17 from 10am to 1pm at Northampton Valley Country Club. There will be exhibitors from state, federal, county, and local agencies offering information on various programs available to assist seniors. There will also be health screenings, senior SEPTA key card processing station, a prescription take-back on site, and much more.\nIf you are not already subscribed to this newsletter please sign up here\n.\nHarrisburg Office\n351 Main Capitol\nHarrisburg, PA 17120\nPhone: 717-787-5072\nLanghorne Office\n370 East Maple Avenue, Suite 203\nLanghorne, PA 19047\nM-F: 9AM to 4:30 PM\nPhone: 215-638-1784\nWant to change how you receive these emails?\nYou can\nupdate your preferences\nor\nunsubscribe\n2026 © Senate of Pennsylvania |\nhttps://senatorfarry.com\n|\nPrivacy Policy",
    "ai_summary": {
      "summary": "Senator Farry's newsletter covers several community events he attended in his district, including the reopening of a renamed bridge over Neshaminy Creek, a birthday memorial event for a child who died in an accident, presenting a Senate citation to a local nonprofit leader, attending two charity walk/run events, and announcing an upcoming senior resources expo on September 17.",
      "action_type": "other",
      "topics": [
        "infrastructure",
        "healthcare",
        "other"
      ],
      "spin_flag": true
    }
  },
