ing annual scholarships to local daycares and camps.\n2026 Woods Services Humanitarian Award\nI was proud to honor Kimberly Permar, Executive Director of Bucks County Health Improvement Partnership (BCHIP), with a Pennsylvania Senate citation for being named the 2026 Woods Humanitarian at Woods System of Care Run earlier this month.\nKim’s advocacy on behalf of Woods System of Care projects has increased access to mental health services and attainable housing across Bucks County. This award is a testament to her dedication as she truly exemplifies the spirit of community.\nKimberly and I are pictured here with Woods System of Care President and CEO Tine Hansen-Turton and Woods System of Care Senior Executive VP/Chief Legal and Governance Officer Simon Kimmelman.\nBAPS Charities Spirit of Service Walk/Runs\nI was proud to join two BAPS Charities Spirit of Service Walk-Runs during the last weekend of May.\nThe first event was held at Falls Township Community Park supporting the Middletown Community Foundation. The next morning, Lions Pride Park in Warrington hosted the event benefiting the Warrington Township Police Department Shop with a Cop program.\nBAPS Charities does an incredible job bringing people together through service and support for local communities. Thank you to everyone who walked, ran, volunteered, and contributed to these great causes.\nSave The Date for Our Senior Expo\nOur annual Senior Expo will be held on September 17 from 10am to 1pm at Northampton Valley Country Club. There will be exhibitors from state, federal, county, and local agencies offering information on various programs available to assist seniors. There will also be health screenings, senior SEPTA key card processing station, a prescription take-back on site, and much more.\nIf you are not already subscribed to this newsletter please sign up here\n.\nHarrisburg Office\n351 Main Capitol\nHarrisburg, PA 17120\nPhone: 717-787-5072\nLanghorne Office\n370 East Maple Avenue, Suite 203\nLanghorne, PA 19047\nM-F: 9AM to 4:30 PM\nPhone: 215-638-1784\nWant to change how you receive these emails?\nYou can\nupdate your preferences\nor\nunsubscribe\n2026 © Senate of Pennsylvania |\nhttps://senatorfarry.com\n|\nPrivacy Policy",
    "ai_summary": {
      "summary": "Senator Farry attended a bridge reopening ceremony for a Vietnam War veteran-named bridge in Bucks County, participated in a birthday memorial event for a deceased child, presented a Senate citation to a local nonprofit leader, attended two charity walk/run events, and announced an upcoming Senior Expo in September 2026. These are routine constituent engagement and ceremonial activities, with no legislation introduced or voted on.",
